   185→// [Sync Streams] Helper that lets the input ncclStreams to wait for the current
   186→// stream. NCCL communications run on ncclStreams, but input tensors are
   187→// allocated on different streams (i.e., current streams). Communications on
   188→// ncclStreams cannot start before pending input tensor ops on current streams
   189→// finish. Otherwise, ops on two streams might read/write same tensors
   190→// concurrently.
   191→//
   192→// The synchronization above alone is not enough. We also need to make sure
   193→// input tensors are not freed before their usages on ncclStreams finish. This
   194→// can be achieved by calling c10::cuda::CUDACachingAllocator::recordStream,
   195→// which remembers the usage stream (ncclStream), creates an event on the usage
   196→// stream when GC attempts to free the input tensor, and delays GC until that
   197→// event is done.
   198→void syncStream(
   199→    at::Device& device,
   200→    at::cuda::CUDAEvent& ncclEvent,
   201→    at::cuda::CUDAStream& ncclStream) {
   202→  ncclEvent.record(at::cuda::getCurrentCUDAStream(device.index()));
   203→  ncclEvent.block(ncclStream);
   204→}
